90
00:08:13,821 --> 00:08:16,517
I was supposed to have
that check by now.

91
00:08:16,624 --> 00:08:18,558
Why are they coming out again?

92
00:08:18,659 --> 00:08:22,789
They need to take another look around.
Take more samples, run more tests.

93
00:08:22,897 --> 00:08:26,993
This reimbursement process
is really pissing me off.

94
00:09:09,477 --> 00:09:11,377
How can you drink that stuff?

95
00:09:13,047 --> 00:09:17,416
- It's free.
- They delivered a new truckload.

96
00:09:17,518 --> 00:09:18,985
Check it out.

97
00:09:20,188 --> 00:09:22,088
And these hats.
Want one?

98
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:29,821
Want to party
at the aqueduct tonight?

99
00:09:30,932 --> 00:09:32,263
Come on!

100
00:09:33,367 --> 00:09:36,302
The only party I heard about
was the one in your panties.

101
00:09:36,404 --> 00:09:38,872
There's no way there could be
a party in my panties.

102
00:09:38,973 --> 00:09:40,770
Why not?

103
00:09:40,875 --> 00:09:43,070
Because I'm not wearing any.

104
00:09:47,615 --> 00:09:49,549
Have a good day, Haley.

105
00:09:52,253 --> 00:09:54,153
Watch your head.

106
00:09:55,823 --> 00:09:58,314
We'll get a report to you ASAP.

107
00:10:00,695 --> 00:10:02,822
She likes you.

108
00:10:02,930 --> 00:10:04,329
Yeah, right!

109
00:10:04,432 --> 00:10:07,060
I'm serious.
I think you're in there.

110
00:10:07,168 --> 00:10:08,567
Whatever.

111
00:10:09,837 --> 00:10:11,065
Bad news.

112
00:10:11,172 --> 00:10:13,299
- What?
- We're in a holding pattern.

113
00:10:13,407 --> 00:10:17,366
The insurance claim hasn't been
processed. They have to run more tests.

114
00:10:20,581 --> 00:10:24,950
She's gonna stay like that for a while.
I'll give you a call when I have work.

115
00:10:25,052 --> 00:10:29,216
Think I can catch a ride with you into
Peaksville? I need to pick up paint.

116
00:10:29,323 --> 00:10:30,915
Yeah, sure.

117
00:10:32,126 --> 00:10:37,120
So much for that job.
I was counting on that motel money.

118
00:10:37,231 --> 00:10:41,827
- You can help me fix up the ocean park.
- You gonna pay me ten bucks an hour?

119
00:10:43,337 --> 00:10:44,736
Fucking Ely, man!

120
00:11:00,421 --> 00:11:03,857
What are you doing?
What did you just blow up?

121
00:11:03,958 --> 00:11:06,324
A canoe.

122
00:11:06,427 --> 00:11:09,328
- It's just an old canoe.
- You can't blow up my dad's canoes.

123
00:11:09,430 --> 00:11:13,196
They're sitting here deteriorating.
I'm speeding up the process.

124
00:11:13,301 --> 00:11:16,134
They're not just sitting here.
Can't you see I'm fixing up the place?

125
00:11:24,912 --> 00:11:26,209
Shit! Keeler.

126
00:11:26,314 --> 00:11:28,441
You're busted.

127
00:11:32,186 --> 00:11:34,518
All right, Elizabeth, let's go.

128
00:11:34,622 --> 00:11:36,886
- You can't arrest me.
- Watch me. You boys see it?

129
00:11:36,991 --> 00:11:39,152
- Just heard it.
- You know the drill.

130
00:11:41,429 --> 00:11:44,262
- I didn't do it.
- You don't say?

131
00:11:44,365 --> 00:11:46,265
Goddamn malicious.

132
00:11:46,367 --> 00:11:49,063
Just takes one to spoil the whole lot.
You know that?

133
00:11:50,104 --> 00:11:52,698
Think he'll make a good sheriff?

134
00:11:52,807 --> 00:11:56,504
He's all right.
You'd make a better one.

135
00:11:56,610 --> 00:11:59,135
She could've blown
her fucking arms off.

136
00:12:07,521 --> 00:12:09,580
Take that stupid hat off!

137
00:12:10,691 --> 00:12:12,591
You all have a good day.

138
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:20,194
I'm gonna get these new fixtures.
You wouldn't believe them.

139
00:12:22,870 --> 00:12:25,600
You put your hands under the faucet
and the water flows.

140
00:12:25,706 --> 00:12:30,109
It's like they got little eyes.
It's like magic.

141
00:12:30,211 --> 00:12:32,805
The water is always
the perfect temperature.

142
00:12:32,913 --> 00:12:35,905
What if I want cold water?

143
00:12:36,016 --> 00:12:38,450
Why do you gotta be so negative?

144
00:12:38,552 --> 00:12:40,520
It was great.

145
00:12:40,621 --> 00:12:42,885
Hey, yes indeed!

146
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:45,959
The world's largest ice cream cone
right out here!

147
00:12:46,060 --> 00:12:47,960
Dessert in the desert!

148
00:12:48,062 --> 00:12:50,895
Looks so real!
Be great to have a ladder.

149
00:12:50,998 --> 00:12:53,398
You could dive into it
and eat it.

150
00:12:53,501 --> 00:12:55,469
That's incredible. Look at that.

151
00:12:55,569 --> 00:12:56,797
It's gorgeous.

152
00:12:56,904 --> 00:13:01,102
It's great. Want an ice cream?
I'll get you one.

153
00:13:01,208 --> 00:13:04,644
Hey, nice shot.

154
00:13:05,913 --> 00:13:08,177
Can I get two cones, please?

155
00:13:10,184 --> 00:13:12,584
It really looks neat.
Neat thing.

156
00:13:12,686 --> 00:13:15,814
Looks bigger than it does
in photographs. Great.

157
00:13:15,923 --> 00:13:20,121
Can either of you tell me
where I can find Mr. Baxter?

158
00:13:20,227 --> 00:13:22,161
He passed away.

159
00:13:25,433 --> 00:13:27,492
- When?
- Six months ago.

160
00:13:28,569 --> 00:13:31,003
Fire at the motel.
It was an accident.

161
00:13:31,105 --> 00:13:33,232
- I had no idea.
- Why should you have?

162
00:13:33,340 --> 00:13:36,901
Because I'm a professor
of cultural studies.

163
00:13:37,011 --> 00:13:40,742
I have a course in pop culture
and the roadside attraction.

164
00:13:40,848 --> 00:13:45,410
We talk about Mr. Baxter in my class.
The giant ice cream cone and ocean park.

165
00:13:45,519 --> 00:13:48,647
Was even putting together a photo book.
Sort of a coffee-table book.

166
00:13:48,756 --> 00:13:50,815
It'll be $1.30.

167
00:13:50,925 --> 00:13:54,827
It's a shame.
I'm sorry he's gone.

168
00:13:54,929 --> 00:13:57,159
- Dad!
- Go more to your left.

169
00:13:57,264 --> 00:14:00,597
- Your other left.
- The sun's in my eyes.

170
00:14:00,701 --> 00:14:03,329
Go back left.

171
00:14:04,438 --> 00:14:05,837
That's too big.

172
00:14:05,940 --> 00:14:09,000
Look up. Can you give us a smile?
Okay, good.

173
00:14:24,091 --> 00:14:26,116
Keeler, what is going on?

174
00:14:27,595 --> 00:14:30,120
She blew up a canoe, sir.

175
00:14:30,231 --> 00:14:34,600
Elizabeth Marie Jackson, is this true?
Did you blow up another canoe?

176
00:14:34,702 --> 00:14:36,169
Maybe.

177
00:14:37,071 --> 00:14:41,508
Let her out. She's a kid! You're locking
up my daughter like she's a criminal!

178
00:14:41,609 --> 00:14:45,807
- She made and detonated a bomb.
- A bomb?

179
00:14:45,913 --> 00:14:49,076
I'm breaking the law
by not reporting this!

180
00:14:49,183 --> 00:14:51,845
Exhibit A. The lighter.

181
00:14:51,952 --> 00:14:54,648
She's got a couple of M-80s
up her sleeves!

182
00:14:54,755 --> 00:14:58,452
M-80s? Exhibit B.
The Polaroid picture.

183
00:14:58,559 --> 00:15:01,653
The canoe was in a million pieces.

184
00:15:01,762 --> 00:15:06,825
You know, I thought you really wanted
this sherif's job in Peaksville.

185
00:15:06,934 --> 00:15:10,802
It's so close.
Be a shame to lose it all...

186
00:15:10,905 --> 00:15:12,873
because of a few firecrackers!

187
00:15:25,986 --> 00:15:28,853
He has to replace Keeler with someone.
Why not you?

188
00:15:28,956 --> 00:15:32,551
- Remember when we slashed his tires?
- Yeah.

189
00:15:32,660 --> 00:15:35,424
And he couldn't respond
to that ten-car pileup?

190
00:15:35,529 --> 00:15:38,157
He knows I tagged up the aqueduct.
I'm a criminal. I can't be a deputy.

191
00:15:38,265 --> 00:15:42,725
Everyone did that. We were 12! The
sherifffucked around when he was a kid.

192
00:15:44,705 --> 00:15:46,104
What the heck?

193
00:15:50,344 --> 00:15:52,437
Ely's out of control!

194
00:15:54,582 --> 00:15:57,016
What the hell was that?

195
00:16:02,089 --> 00:16:03,989
I don't know.

196
00:16:36,190 --> 00:16:38,488
Anybody hurt?

197
00:16:38,592 --> 00:16:40,492
What's that smell?

198
00:16:40,594 --> 00:16:42,459
It's coming from the truck.

199
00:16:42,563 --> 00:16:44,360
Fucking A!

200
00:16:46,567 --> 00:16:48,762
You're a lucky man.

201
00:16:48,869 --> 00:16:54,000
There's nothing like a close brush with
death to knock the life back into you.

202
00:16:54,108 --> 00:16:56,576
My arm is hurt.

203
00:16:56,677 --> 00:16:59,145
What's that smell? What is that?

204
00:16:59,246 --> 00:17:02,409
- It's dog shit.
- The secret ingredient to Empire Cola.

205
00:17:02,516 --> 00:17:05,451
It's in its concentrated form.
I got it all over me.

206
00:17:05,552 --> 00:17:07,611
What the hell is in it?

207
00:17:07,721 --> 00:17:10,952
That's classified information.
Only a few people know.

208
00:17:11,058 --> 00:17:13,925
They're not even allowed
on the same airplane.

209
00:17:14,028 --> 00:17:16,019
I'm not one of them.

210
00:17:17,231 --> 00:17:19,358
- How'd it happen?
- Officer?

211
00:17:19,466 --> 00:17:22,958
- I saw the whole thing.
- Don't leave. I need to ask questions.

212
00:17:25,506 --> 00:17:27,269
I'm going to the car.

213
00:17:27,374 --> 00:17:29,638
Aren't you just the coolest?

214
00:17:32,112 --> 00:17:34,637
Can I help you with something?

215
00:17:53,767 --> 00:17:56,736
- She has a cell phone?
- She must be from L.A.

216
00:17:58,672 --> 00:18:00,936
Shit!

217
00:18:01,041 --> 00:18:03,976
I'm in fucking Egypt!

218
00:18:07,915 --> 00:18:10,884
Seems like her biscuit
could use a little buttering.

219
00:18:10,984 --> 00:18:13,418
- Excuse me!
- Not by me.

220
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:15,215
It's just an observation.

221
00:18:17,424 --> 00:18:19,585
Shit.

222
00:18:19,693 --> 00:18:21,092
Dorks.

223
00:18:23,464 --> 00:18:25,557
- Seems like a bitch.
- You don't know her.

224
00:18:25,666 --> 00:18:27,861
That's why I said, "seems like."

225
00:18:31,205 --> 00:18:33,366
Hello. I'm nearing menopause.

226
00:18:33,474 --> 00:18:38,343
Mr. Jason,
your N.C.I.C. Came out clean.

227
00:18:38,445 --> 00:18:40,538
That's National Crime
Information Center.

228
00:18:40,647 --> 00:18:43,115
Just checking to see
if you got any outstanding warrants.

229
00:18:43,217 --> 00:18:46,209
I don't get it. You're investigating me
because I witnessed an accident?

230
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:48,345
I guess you'll be heading back
to San Francisco.

231
00:18:48,455 --> 00:18:50,889
- Nice town?
- Great.

232
00:18:50,991 --> 00:18:53,721
Too many cars,
but that's true everywhere.

233
00:18:53,827 --> 00:18:55,294
Been there long?

234
00:18:55,395 --> 00:18:57,693
No. I moved there
after my divorce.

235
00:18:57,798 --> 00:18:59,891
My daughter still lives
with her mother in L.A.

236
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,729
L.A.P.D!

237
00:19:01,835 --> 00:19:03,564
The greatest.

238
00:19:03,670 --> 00:19:06,230
We'll contact you
if we need any more information.

239
00:19:06,340 --> 00:19:07,864
Sign right here.

240
00:19:16,316 --> 00:19:20,150
Are you trying to get me thrown in jail
for disturbing the peace?

241
00:19:20,254 --> 00:19:23,382
Jesus Christ, Dad. I thought my clothes
were gonna go out of style.

242
00:19:23,490 --> 00:19:26,084
No fear of that.
We're gonna get something to eat.

243
00:19:26,193 --> 00:19:30,926
- Can we eat somewhere else?
- Sheriff said this place was fantastic.

244
00:19:31,031 --> 00:19:34,330
- What's the fun of having a body if...
