980
01:13:40,677 --> 01:13:43,373
He left a note saying
how sorry he was.

981
01:13:44,148 --> 01:13:47,083
But he didn't say why he did it.

982
01:13:49,453 --> 01:13:51,853
I'm sure it was
because of this place.

983
01:13:57,461 --> 01:14:00,453
Just wanted everyone
to remember him as...

984
01:14:00,564 --> 01:14:02,794
someone who was happy.

985
01:14:05,069 --> 01:14:07,299
He wasn't happy, though.
He wasn't happy at all.

986
01:14:11,308 --> 01:14:14,368
I couldn't let him
just go like that.

987
01:14:14,478 --> 01:14:17,208
Everyone would have
called him a failure.

988
01:14:23,187 --> 01:14:25,985
I took him down
and put him in bed.

989
01:14:35,432 --> 01:14:37,832
Then I set fire to the place.

990
01:16:14,131 --> 01:16:16,031
Look at what I'm doing.

991
01:16:16,133 --> 01:16:20,035
I dug up some old photographs,
so I thought I'd make a new album.

992
01:16:21,438 --> 01:16:23,929
I like this one.
This one's good.

993
01:16:33,550 --> 01:16:34,881
What's wrong?

994
01:17:04,548 --> 01:17:07,483
I could blow up your dad's car
if you wanna stay longer.

995
01:17:07,584 --> 01:17:09,779
Thanks.

996
01:17:09,886 --> 01:17:11,251
- Where's Blue?
- Said he'd meet us here.

997
01:17:11,355 --> 01:17:14,415
Blue is probably out
squatting in the bushes.

998
01:17:14,524 --> 01:17:18,324
- Maybe he shouldn't have come out.
- It's the painkillers. He'll be fine.

999
01:17:18,428 --> 01:17:20,919
Didn't you see what happened
to the detective?

1000
01:17:21,031 --> 01:17:23,056
You're not supposed to
mix those things with alcohol.

1001
01:17:23,166 --> 01:17:26,260
You shut down your respiratory system,
and now everyone's a doctor.

1002
01:17:26,370 --> 01:17:31,239
- I'm celebrating our newfound freedom.
- Is this gonna get boring again?

1003
01:17:31,341 --> 01:17:34,071
- I liked having those freaks around.
- What do you mean?

1004
01:17:34,177 --> 01:17:36,771
- They shot me.
- It'd be different if you were dead.

1005
01:17:36,880 --> 01:17:39,713
You guys, it's been
really cool being here.

1006
01:17:39,816 --> 01:17:41,283
I'll drink to that.

1007
01:17:44,254 --> 01:17:47,746
What's the chance he'll get here?

1008
01:18:04,041 --> 01:18:06,908
I thought I was
doing the right thing.

1009
01:18:07,010 --> 01:18:08,910
For my dad.

1010
01:18:10,013 --> 01:18:11,913
I'm sorry.

1011
01:18:13,817 --> 01:18:16,047
I'll help you rebuild it.

1012
01:18:20,490 --> 01:18:24,153
Billy, are you covered
against arson?

1013
01:18:26,763 --> 01:18:28,731
Yeah.

1014
01:18:29,700 --> 01:18:31,600
It's just...

1015
01:19:00,297 --> 01:19:01,992
So...

1016
01:19:04,234 --> 01:19:06,828
now that we know everything...

1017
01:19:11,208 --> 01:19:14,200
what do you say we just pretend
that we know nothing?

1018
01:19:26,056 --> 01:19:28,115
- Hi, there.
- Hi.

1019
01:19:29,826 --> 01:19:31,987
He's all yours.

1020
01:19:35,532 --> 01:19:39,059
So, how'd it go?

1021
01:19:39,169 --> 01:19:42,161
Got a new job
building the motel.

1022
01:19:42,272 --> 01:19:45,241
- Cool.
- When do you leave?

1023
01:19:45,342 --> 01:19:47,435
About 20 minutes.

1024
01:19:50,414 --> 01:19:52,473
Let's go for a ride then.

1025
01:20:05,862 --> 01:20:08,558
There's a Sterling Brock
on the phone for you.

1026
01:20:12,769 --> 01:20:15,897
- Can you take a message?
- Okay.

1027
01:20:16,006 --> 01:20:18,600
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

1028
01:20:19,743 --> 01:20:21,301
All right.

1029
01:21:27,777 --> 01:21:30,109
What's up, poster girl?

1030
01:21:30,213 --> 01:21:34,172
Deputy, huh?
You won't ever arrest me, will you?

1031
01:21:35,619 --> 01:21:37,018
Probably not.

1032
01:21:38,788 --> 01:21:40,983
Telly, this is Pete.
I'm number one.

1033
01:21:41,091 --> 01:21:43,582
I'm number one,
you fucking scumbag!

1034
01:21:43,693 --> 01:21:46,821
And when my brother starts racing,
you'll be number three.

1035
01:22:11,354 --> 01:22:13,879
Kids went for a ride.
They're coming right back.

1036
01:22:13,990 --> 01:22:17,391
I just came by
to say thanks for everything.

1037
01:22:17,494 --> 01:22:21,055
Well, you're welcome.
It was nice having you here.

1038
01:22:21,164 --> 01:22:23,359
I was thinking,
next time I come up north...

1039
01:22:23,466 --> 01:22:25,991
if I could maybe
stop by and see you.

1040
01:22:26,102 --> 01:22:28,900
- I'd like that.
- It'd be okay?

1041
01:22:29,005 --> 01:22:29,334
They turned into
these invisible ninjas...

1042
01:22:31,608 --> 01:22:34,168
and they had all these
throwing stars and...

1043
01:22:36,613 --> 01:22:38,513
Holy shit.

1044
01:22:40,584 --> 01:22:43,348
- What was that?
- That's Ely.

1045
01:22:43,453 --> 01:22:45,045
Oh, shit.

1046
01:22:45,155 --> 01:22:47,055
That was the big one.

1047
01:23:10,246 --> 01:23:12,146
I'll drive.

1048
01:23:39,609 --> 01:23:41,804
She's in for it now.

1049
